OL,6,FIn an email exchange between civil
OL,7,Fservants in March 2020, then head of
OL,8,Fthe Northern Ireland Civil Service,
OL,9,FSir David Sterling, noted Ms O'Neill's
OL,10,Ffrustration at "having little power or
OL,11,Finfluence over the health service".
OL,13,FHe wrote that Ms Foster recognised the
OL,14,Foperational independence of the health
OL,15,Fminister but was also "frustrated at
OL,16,Fthe lack of information" coming out of
OL,17,Fthe Department of Health and "frequent
OL,18,Fsurprises", such as an announcement
OL,19,Fabout hospital visits ending.
